===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒrəl|-ɒrəl]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

# of or relating to principles of [[right]] and [[wrong]] in behavior, especially for teaching right behavior
#: '''''moral''' judgments'', ''a '''moral''' poem''
# conforming to a standard of [[right]] behavior; sanctioned by or operative on one's conscience or ethical judgment
#: ''a '''moral''' obligation''
# capable of right and wrong action
#: ''a '''moral''' agent''
# probable but not proved
#: ''a '''moral''' certainty''
# positively affecting the mind, confidence or will
#: ''a '''moral''' victory'', '''''moral''' support''

====Synonyms====
* (''conforming to a standard of right behavior''): [[ethical]], [[virtuous]], [[righteous]], [[noble]]
* (''provable but not proved''): [[virtual]]

